12/Jul/24 9:54 AM;60957172a56f2f006f65f1e9;Some changes have been made to the branch per Erichâ€™s and Yungâ€™s suggestionsin the PR:

* Constant names have been assigned to unassigned values. e.g 120 is now AcVolNominal, 60 is now AcFreqNominal. Similar cases have been resolved.
* All errors reported in the plugintests have been fixed to be in the snake format.
* {{golangci-lint run --fix}} has been used to fix some of the linter issues. This command does not work on my NUC, so the linter fixes are done on the PXI.
* Functions (e.g. GridVoltageGoodCheck, GridVoltageBadCheck, MantaRelayClosedCheck, MantaRelayOpenCheck and others) have been created and added to read_test_data.go to reduce code repetition in the compliance tests.

To-do:
*  Modify the functions (e.g. GridVoltageGoodCheck, MantaRelayClosedCheck and similar others) to export the values of the voltages/current/alarm/relay state so they can be used to validate tests. This will prevent code repetition and 
* Write more functions in read_test_data.go to reduce code repetition in the plugintests.
* Fix all implementations of {{for time.Since(time.Now()) < vol.ReadSignalDuration}} to use {{for time.Since(begin) < vol.ReadSignalDuration}} where {{begin := time.Now()}}. Else, every loop with time.Now() will re-evaluated and return a new time for the start of the current loop. This explained why the loop continued to run and the logic didnâ€™t work as expected.
* Update constant names to follow style guide.
* Fix linter issues.

Blue Marlin FW Release Testing: June 2024
column30:
Execution of the release test set and pre-compliance test set for Blue Marlin System FW received in June 20th, 2024.
The release candidates tested are:
Manta: 0.9.5 - RC2, RC3
BMU: 0.2.1-RC1, RC2, RC3
INV: 1.10.0-RC2, RC-4
This testing is done to close the loop on these release candidates and ensure stable and reliable FW for alpha sites, test systems, and production.
column97: 24-Q2-KR7.2: Validate BM Firmware Release in 48 Hours
column175:
26/Jun/24 7:34 AM;5e6aa6b89abcc30ce60ca4ef;we are currently blocked on release testing with a [Inverter bug|https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgeneracet.atlassian.net%2Fbrowse%2FR2IF-322&data=05%7C02%7CJoe.Wardwell%40generac.com%7C939309b4eb5e4ff2d75708dc95d9051d%7C3a720757c2fd40b096eb840507006544%7C0%7C0%7C638550006545504768%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=dLorGtAFf45KQlFdaYi5zQbFfCoWByfwh7m%2FADOZJB4%3D&reserved=0] that wonâ€™t allow our systems to enable without an undervoltage alarm. This has been present on all RCs we have tested. This issue was repeated on both systems in Waukesha, and we are actively debugging the issue with Tony N.'s help. Details and links to the issue are in our [Issue Summary|https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgeneracet.atlassian.net%2Fwiki%2Fspaces%2FCTET%2Fpages%2F403570689%2FR2%2BFW%2B-%2BJune%2B24%23Issue-Summary&data=05%7C02%7CJoe.Wardwell%40generac.com%7C939309b4eb5e4ff2d75708dc95d9051d%7C3a720757c2fd40b096eb840507006544%7C0%7C0%7C638550006545515929%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=japYCXUhJgtb%2FAOdCidSrYByB8uFT%2FssmiZ7sfK0gw4%3D&reserved=0] as well.

When we got to the end of our debugging sessions today without a resolution, so we rolled back FW on INV and BMU on our Voltron system to run more automated tests and continue to build out/improve/validate them.
Debugging continues the other system we have in Waukesha. When we get a procedure to correct this issue, or a new RC is available we will bring both systems back up to the release and continue testing.
